</tr>
</table>
<p>Tufte also developed <a href="/wiki/Sparkline" title="Sparkline">sparklines</a> — a simple, condensed way to present trends and variation, associated with a measurement such as average <a href="/wiki/Temperature" title="Temperature">temperature</a> or <a href="/wiki/Stock_market" title="Stock market">stock market</a> activity. These are often used as elements of a <a href="/wiki/Small_multiple" title="Small multiple">Small multiple</a> with several lines used together. Tufte explains the sparkline as a kind of "word" that conveys rich information without breaking the flow of a sentence or paragraph made of other "words" both visual and conventional.</p>
<p><a name="Bibliography" id="Bibliography"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Edward_Tufte&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5" title="Edit section: Bibliography">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Bibliography</span></h2>
<p>Tufte's Yale PhD thesis was <i>The Civil Rights Movement and Its Opposition</i> (1968).</p>
<p>Early in his career, Tufte wrote several books about using statistics to analyze political issues:</p>
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFDahlTufte.2C_Edward_R.1973"><a href="/wiki/Robert_A._Dahl" title="Robert A. Dahl">Dahl, Robert</a>; Tufte, Edward R. (1973). <i>Size &amp; Democracy</i>. Stanford University Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0804708347" class="internal">ISBN 0804708347</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Size+%26+Democracy&amp;rft.aulast=Dahl&amp;rft.aufirst=Robert&amp;rft.au=Dahl%2C+Robert&amp;rft.au=Tufte%2C+Edward+R.&amp;rft.date=1973&amp;rft.pub=Stanford+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0804708347&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Edward_Tufte"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFTufte1974">Tufte, Edward R. (1974-08-05). <i>Data Analysis for Politics and Policy</i>. Prentice Hall College Div. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0131975250" class="internal">ISBN 0131975250</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Data+Analysis+for+Politics+and+Policy&amp;rft.aulast=Tufte&amp;rft.aufirst=Edward+R.&amp;rft.au=Tufte%2C+Edward+R.&amp;rft.date=1974-08-05&amp;rft.pub=Prentice+Hall+College+Div&amp;rft.isbn=0131975250&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Edward_Tufte"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>
<ul>
<li>Tufte notes on his website that a second edition of this book is likely.</li>
<li>Tufte now owns the copyright and has made a <a href="http://www.edwardtufte.com/tufte/dapp/" class="external text" title="http://www.edwardtufte.com/tufte/dapp/" rel="nofollow">free pdf of DAPP available on his website</a>.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFTufte1978">Tufte, Edward R. (1978). <i>Political Control of the Economy</i>. Princeton University Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0691075948" class="internal">ISBN 0691075948</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Political+Control+of+the+Economy&amp;rft.aulast=Tufte&amp;rft.aufirst=Edward+R.&amp;rft.au=Tufte%2C+Edward+R.&amp;rft.date=1978&amp;rft.pub=Princeton+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0691075948&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Edward_Tufte"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
</ul>
<p>The core of Tufte's work documents how to best display different forms of information with copious examples and commentary:</p>
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFTufte2001">Tufte, Edward R. (2001) [1983]. <i>The Visual Display of Quantitative Information</i> (2nd ed.). Cheshire, CT: Graphics Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0961392142" class="internal">ISBN 0961392142</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Visual+Display+of+Quantitative+Information&amp;rft.aulast=Tufte&amp;rft.aufirst=Edward+R.&amp;rft.au=Tufte%2C+Edward+R.&amp;rft.date=2001&amp;rft.edition=2nd&amp;rft.place=Cheshire%2C+CT&amp;rft.pub=Graphics+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0961392142&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Edward_Tufte"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFTufte1990">Tufte, Edward R. (1990). <i>Envisioning Information</i>. Cheshire, CT: Graphics Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0961392118" class="internal">ISBN 0961392118</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Envisioning+Information&amp;rft.aulast=Tufte&amp;rft.aufirst=Edward+R.&amp;rft.au=Tufte%2C+Edward+R.&amp;rft.date=1990&amp;rft.place=Cheshire%2C+CT&amp;rft.pub=Graphics+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0961392118&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Edward_Tufte"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFTufte1997">Tufte, Edward R. (1997). <i>Visual Explanations: Images and Quantities, Evidence and Narrative</i>. Cheshire, CT: Graphics Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0961392126" class="internal">ISBN 0961392126</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Visual+Explanations%3A+Images+and+Quantities%2C+Evidence+and+Narrative&amp;rft.aulast=Tufte&amp;rft.aufirst=Edward+R.&amp;rft.au=Tufte%2C+Edward+R.&amp;rft.date=1997&amp;rft.place=Cheshire%2C+CT&amp;rft.pub=Graphics+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0961392126&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Edward_Tufte"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>
<ul>
<li>Chapter 2 is also published as <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFTufte1997">Tufte, Edward R. (1997). <i>Visual &amp; Statistical Thinking: Displays of Evidence for Decision Making</i>. Cheshire, CT: Graphics Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0961392134" class="internal">ISBN 0961392134</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Visual+%26+Statistical+Thinking%3A+Displays+of+Evidence+for+Decision+Making&amp;rft.aulast=Tufte&amp;rft.aufirst=Edward+R.&amp;rft.au=Tufte%2C+Edward+R.&amp;rft.date=1997&amp;rft.place=Cheshire%2C+CT&amp;rft.pub=Graphics+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0961392134&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Edward_Tufte"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> It contains extensive analysis of <a href="/wiki/John_Snow_(physician)" title="John Snow (physician)">Dr John Snow's</a> intervention into the cholera epidemic in London in 1854 and of the <a href="/wiki/STS-51-L" title="STS-51-L"><i>Challenger</i> disaster</a> of 1986.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFTufte2003">Tufte, Edward R. (2003). "<a href="http://www.wired.com/wired/archive/11.09/ppt2.html" class="external text" title="http://www.wired.com/wired/archive/11.09/ppt2.html" rel="nofollow">PowerPoint is evil</a>". <i>Wired</i> <b>11</b> (9). <a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Serial_Number" title="International Standard Serial Number">ISSN</a> <a href="http://worldcat.org/issn/1059-1028" class="external text" title="http://worldcat.org/issn/1059-1028" rel="nofollow">1059-1028</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.wired.com/wired/archive/11.09/ppt2.html" class="external free" title="http://www.wired.com/wired/archive/11.09/ppt2.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.wired.com/wired/archive/11.09/ppt2.html</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=PowerPoint+is+evil&amp;rft.jtitle=Wired&amp;rft.aulast=Tufte&amp;rft.aufirst=Edward+R.&amp;rft.au=Tufte%2C+Edward+R.&amp;rft.date=2003&amp;rft.volume=11&amp;rft.issue=9&amp;rft.issn=1059-1028&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2Fwired%2Farchive%2F11.09%2Fppt2.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Edward_Tufte"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFTufte2006">Tufte, Edward R. (2006) [2003]. <i><a href="http://www.edwardtufte.com/tufte/powerpoint" class="external text" title="http://www.edwardtufte.com/tufte/powerpoint" rel="nofollow">The Cognitive Style of PowerPoint</a></i> (2nd ed.). Cheshire, CT: Graphics Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0961392169" class="internal">ISBN 0961392169</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.edwardtufte.com/tufte/powerpoint" class="external free" title="http://www.edwardtufte.com/tufte/powerpoint" rel="nofollow">http://www.edwardtufte.com/tufte/powerpoint</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Cognitive+Style+of+PowerPoint&amp;rft.aulast=Tufte&amp;rft.aufirst=Edward+R.&amp;rft.au=Tufte%2C+Edward+R.&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.edition=2nd&amp;rft.place=Cheshire%2C+CT&amp;rft.pub=Graphics+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0961392169&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.edwardtufte.com%2Ftufte%2Fpowerpoint&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Edward_Tufte"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFTufte2006">Tufte, Edward R. (2006). <i>Beautiful Evidence</i>. Cheshire, CT: Graphics Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0961392177" class="internal">ISBN 0961392177</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Beautiful+Evidence&amp;rft.aulast=Tufte&amp;rft.aufirst=Edward+R.&amp;rft.au=Tufte%2C+Edward+R.&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.place=Cheshire%2C+CT&amp;rft.pub=Graphics+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0961392177&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Edward_Tufte"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
</ul>
